President Obama met with members of the Congressional Asian Pacific American Caucus (CAPAC) to discuss issues facing the Asian American and Pacific Islander communities. The President thanked the Caucus for their work in Congress and expressed his commitment to continuing to work with them. The Caucus brought up several points for discussion, including the diversity of the federal judiciary, the Affordable Care Act, immigration reform, and the American Jobs Act. The President pledged to work with Congress to create a streamlined, efficient, and fair immigration system. The meeting was attended by Cabinet Secretary Chris Lu, Deputy Chief of Staff Nancy-Ann DeParle, Director of Intergovernmental Affairs Cecilia Mu√±oz, and Director of the White House AAPI Initiative Kiran Ahuja.